00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,280
Because I'm a bit OCD.

305
00:09:58,280 --> 00:09:59,880
I woke up to see a messy kitchen.

306
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:00,559
It was too much.

307
00:10:02,125 --> 00:10:03,968
(Messy)

308
00:10:09,479 --> 00:10:11,200
I came down and heard that,

309
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:12,880
you know...

310
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:13,599
Tears welling up.

311
00:10:13,599 --> 00:10:14,280
Streaming down.

312
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,599
I started the ball rolling.

313
00:10:15,599 --> 00:10:17,320
I'm sure you'll join in.

314
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,200
I'll be down here

315
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:18,799
(Keep going)
at 8:30 AM.

316
00:10:18,799 --> 00:10:20,640
You can get up at 6:30 AM again.

317
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:24,880
What kind of cuisine do you prefer?

318
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,880
I enjoy Cantonese cuisine.

319
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:28,960
And

320
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:30,919
hotpot.

321
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:32,400
Hotpot?

322
00:10:32,919 --> 00:10:35,119
Wenchang Chicken, Qingyuan Chicken.

323
00:10:35,119 --> 00:10:35,919
I don't mind.

324
00:10:35,919 --> 00:10:36,239
Anything.

325
00:10:38,719 --> 00:10:39,440
So

326
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:42,159
you wrote the poetic lines

327
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:42,760
on the exclusive note?

328
00:10:46,239 --> 00:10:46,960
Poetic lines?

329
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:47,919
Yes.

330
00:10:47,919 --> 00:10:48,960
The one you read yesterday.

331
00:10:50,679 --> 00:10:51,799
(The evening before)
Ten miles of spring breeze

332
00:10:51,799 --> 00:10:53,000
is fated to meet.

333
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,599
Words in perfect sync.

334
00:10:54,599 --> 00:10:56,080
The two words after that

335
00:10:56,559 --> 00:10:58,080
look a bit blurry.

336
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:00,840
You wrote it for Chen Danqi?

337
00:11:01,359 --> 00:11:01,559
Yes.

338
00:11:01,559 --> 00:11:03,159
We had lunch together yesterday.

339
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:04,799
I was guessing.

340
00:11:04,799 --> 00:11:06,280
I said,

341
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,280
"Who wrote this?"

342
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:09,440
And I guessed it was you.

343
00:11:10,559 --> 00:11:12,599
That night when we drew lots,

344
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:13,840
it was funny.

345
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,039
He told me to go there

346
00:11:15,039 --> 00:11:16,640
and take out that card.

347
00:11:17,479 --> 00:11:18,559
After I got there,

348
00:11:19,119 --> 00:11:20,840
the notepad pages were stuck.

349
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,239
I pried that page apart

350
00:11:22,239 --> 00:11:23,200
and pulled it out.

351
00:11:24,599 --> 00:11:25,320
This part

352
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:26,640
is not user-friendly.

353
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:27,440
It's so stiff.

354
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,080
I struggled.

355
00:11:28,235 --> 00:11:36,704
(Choosing the exclusive note)

356
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:40,919
After I tore it open,

357
00:11:40,919 --> 00:11:41,960
all it said was "Danqi".

358
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:42,599
I was like,

359
00:11:42,599 --> 00:11:43,760
"Is that a name? Or a sport?"

360
00:11:45,679 --> 00:11:46,400
Danqi.

361
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:47,640
Danqi.

362
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:48,679
Because both those characters

363
00:11:48,679 --> 00:11:49,760
have multiple pronunciations.

364
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:50,799
I didn't know how to read them.

365
00:11:50,799 --> 00:11:51,400
"Shanqi".

366
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:51,640
Yes.

367
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:52,919
As a surname, it's pronounced "Shan".

368
00:11:52,919 --> 00:11:54,159
If it's a sport.

369
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:55,919
Is it "qi" or "ji"?

370
00:11:55,919 --> 00:11:57,320
I got stuck on that.

371
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:58,599
Too intellectual.

372
00:11:58,599 --> 00:11:59,960
Four possible pronunciations.

373
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,599
Too much education confused you.

374
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,400
Next time, skip the poetic lines.

375
00:12:04,679 --> 00:12:06,280
I was totally confused.

376
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,400
I focused on eating

377
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,559
and didn't pay attention.

378
00:12:08,559 --> 00:12:08,840
Yes.

379
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,599
They asked me about it.

380
00:12:09,599 --> 00:12:10,679
I couldn't figure it out.

381
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,440
Me neither.

382
00:12:13,119 --> 00:12:13,719
Who do you think

383
00:12:13,719 --> 00:12:14,919
it's meant for?

384
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:15,840
I said,

385
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,119
"It's probably

386
00:12:17,119 --> 00:12:18,200
for any other

387
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,479
female participant."

388
00:12:19,479 --> 00:12:19,919
Makes sense.

389
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:21,880
But...

390
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:24,479
Jia Peixuan.

391
00:12:25,239 --> 00:12:25,799
You?

392
00:12:25,799 --> 00:12:26,840
Xiaowen.

393
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,479
I have one note.

394
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:28,520
So it's Xiaowen.

395
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:29,520
Xiaowen got two notes.

396
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:30,719
(Jia Peixuan's note to Xiao Wentao)
Someone likes

397
00:12:30,719 --> 00:12:33,239
Xiaowen's high nose bridge.

398
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:36,239
How do you know
about the "high nose bridge"?

399
00:12:36,239 --> 00:12:36,599
Well...

400
00:12:36,599 --> 00:12:38,359
She wrote it down

401
00:12:38,359 --> 00:12:40,000
in the note.

402
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:40,440
I didn't

403
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:41,599
catch on yesterday.

404
00:12:41,599 --> 00:12:42,719
"Your high nose bridge."

405
00:12:42,719 --> 00:12:43,960
I thought it was

406
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,719
addressed to all three of you.

407
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:48,799
Torn into three parts?

408
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,799
First part for you. Middle for you.

409
00:12:50,799 --> 00:12:51,559
Last third for me.

410
00:12:51,559 --> 00:12:53,039
She likes our high nose bridges.

411
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:54,039
All three of you.

412
00:12:54,039 --> 00:12:55,400
It was for all three of us.

413
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,640
Who's missing?

414
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:00,359
I only asked

415
00:13:00,359 --> 00:13:01,520
Xuehua Bing out.

416
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:03,440
So I didn't expect the notes

417
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,840
to be full of twists.

418
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,320
(Not sitting)
I need to

419
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,799
put it somewhere else.

420
00:13:29,799 --> 00:13:30,440
Where?

421
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:31,280
Let me help you.

422
00:13:33,359 --> 00:13:34,119
Over there?

423
00:13:34,119 --> 00:13:35,039
Better lighting.

424
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:40,000
Like this.

425
00:13:41,359 --> 00:13:41,919
This angle.

426
00:13:41,919 --> 00:13:42,520
It's better.

427
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:43,119
Yeah.

428
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:44,400
Looks good.

429
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:44,719
Okay?

430
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:49,960
Are these all paints?

431
00:13:50,799 --> 00:13:51,479
Yes.

432
00:13:52,599 --> 00:13:53,320
This color is quite nice.

433
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:57,119
I really like this color.

434
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:58,200
It looks like

435
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,479
A Thousand Li of Rivers and Mountains

436
00:13:59,479 --> 00:13:59,880
by Wang Ximeng.

437
00:14:02,679 --> 00:14:03,159
So.

438
00:14:04,239 --> 00:14:07,559
Our daily essentials have arrived.

439
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,400
I bought some racks for everyone.

440
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:12,520
Where has he put them?

441
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:13,559
At the door.

442
00:14:14,559 --> 00:14:14,919
Alright.

443
00:14:14,919 --> 00:14:16,119
Recess.

444
00:14:16,119 --> 00:14:16,719
Do some labor work.

445
00:14:18,799 --> 00:14:19,840
I bought many things.

446
00:14:23,744 --> 00:14:26,165
(Big and small bags)

447
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:27,479
Here

448
00:14:27,479 --> 00:14:28,880
or upstairs?

449
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:29,479
Upstairs?

450
00:14:29,479 --> 00:14:30,719
I think...

451
00:14:30,719 --> 00:14:31,159
Yeah.

452
00:14:31,159 --> 00:14:32,599
Set them by their doors.

453
00:14:32,599 --> 00:14:33,559
What do you think?

454
00:14:33,559 --> 00:14:34,200
Sure.

455
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:34,520
Let's go.

456
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:39,200
Give it to me.

457
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,039
Let's distribute them.

458
00:14:50,039 --> 00:14:51,039
(Handing them out)

459
00:14:51,039 --> 00:14:52,679
So this one goes to the two girls.

460
00:14:52,679 --> 00:14:53,640
(One delivery)
211 has one.

461
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:54,688
(Another delivery)

462
00:14:55,968 --> 00:14:58,304
(Chen and Dong keep delivering)

463
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,119
We are heading out.

464
00:15:02,119 --> 00:15:03,520
Straight to the supermarket.

465
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:03,799
Yes.

466
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:06,440
I'll take your picture.

467
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:07,159
I brought my camera.

468
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:08,400
So fairy-like?

469
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,359
Hold on a second.

470
00:15:10,359 --> 00:15:11,599
I'll adjust the lighting.

471
00:15:11,599 --> 00:15:13,239
Take your time. No rush.

472
00:15:13,239 --> 00:15:13,960
I'll get one too.

473
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,400
Looking handsome.

474
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,679
Take some more.

475
00:15:20,679 --> 00:15:21,239
No need.

476
00:15:21,239 --> 00:15:22,080
It's good enough.

477
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,679
I get really stiff in photos.

478
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,559
You look great.

479
00:15:26,559 --> 00:15:27,479
Who's next?

480
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,159
Come on, let's compete.

481
00:15:29,159 --> 00:15:30,599
Let's see

482
00:15:30,599 --> 00:15:32,239
whose photo Ruita prefers.

483
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:35,200
Let me find the right angle.

484
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:35,960
Wait a minute.

485
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,216
(Xuan VS Tao)

486
00:15:37,216 --> 00:15:37,520
(Tao finding angles)

487
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:38,200
Stay right there.

488
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,679
Stay where you were.

489
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,159
Okay, look at me.

490
00:15:42,159 --> 00:15:43,239
(Still searching for an angle)

491
00:15:43,239 --> 00:15:43,760
Stunning.

492
00:15:43,991 --> 00:15:45,760
(Effortlessly; Still searching)

493
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:46,479
Amazing.

494
00:15:50,159 --> 00:15:52,119
Just like that.

495
00:15:52,119 --> 00:15:53,359
Excuse me, are you a celebrity?

496
00:15:53,359 --> 00:15:54,400
(Great emotional value)
Just like this.

497
00:15:56,119 --> 00:15:57,000
I can't take this anymore.

498
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,840
The introvert is about to flee.

499
00:15:58,840 --> 00:15:59,840
I'm telling you.

500
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:00,479
Seriously.

501
00:16:00,479 --> 00:16:01,960
You look amazing, okay?

502
00:16:03,679 --> 00:16:04,880
Come on.

503
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,400
Ask her for photos.

504
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:06,960
Sorry.

505
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:08,919
Let me see the photos you took.

506
00:16:08,919 --> 00:16:10,159
No need.

507
00:16:11,239 --> 00:16:12,000
I'll take your picture.

508
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:13,039
Are you going?

509
00:16:13,039 --> 00:16:13,479
Want a photo?

510
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:16,359
I want my whole body visible.

511
00:16:16,359 --> 00:16:16,719
Is that fine?

512
00:16:17,159 --> 00:16:17,719
Okay.

513
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:20,599
He wants the cool vibe.

514
00:16:21,479 --> 00:16:22,559
Let me change spots.

515
00:16:22,559 --> 00:16:23,159
Xuan.

516
00:16:23,159 --> 00:16:23,880
Want a photo?

517
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:24,640
I can take yours.

518
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:25,200
It's fine. Later.

519
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,280
I'll take his photo first.

520
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:27,960
He hasn't gotten his shot.

521
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,119
I have to get his picture done.

522
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:31,799
Alright.

523
00:16:31,799 --> 00:16:33,599
Lower your head as you did before.

524
00:16:33,599 --> 00:16:35,119
Not too much. Just a little bit.

525
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:36,239
Okay.

526
00:16:36,239 --> 00:16:36,599
Cool.

527
00:16:38,039 --> 00:16:39,640
Okay, full body now.

528
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,400
Don't lower your head.

529
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:41,919
Another pose.

530
00:16:42,479 --> 00:16:43,320
Okay.

531
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,159
Thank you.

532
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:49,239
This one.

533
00:16:49,239 --> 00:16:49,679
Stunning.

534
00:16:49,679 --> 00:16:50,239
Great angle.

535
00:16:50,799 --> 00:16:52,679
I'll get a third angle then.

536
00:16:53,599 --> 00:16:54,760
I'll pose too.

537
00:16:56,073 --> 00:16:59,320
(Picture within a picture)

538
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:00,039
This is so much fun.

539
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:01,840
Get closer.

540
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:02,760
Or we won't fit in the frame.

541
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:03,919
Yes, get closer.

542
00:17:03,919 --> 00:17:04,920
Get really close.

543
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,239
Or we won't fit.

544
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:10,319
Alright.

545
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:10,920
You're amazing.

546
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:11,439
One more shot.

547
00:17:11,439 --> 00:17:13,319
Lower it a bit and it's perfect.

548
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:19,479
Amazing.

549
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:21,400
Let's go.

550
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:25,760
So cozy.

551
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:26,359
So cozy.

552
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:30,160
So relaxing today.

553
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:31,280
So soothing.

554
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:43,959
You're so good at taking pictures.

555
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:44,880
Look.

556
00:17:45,479 --> 00:17:45,839
Don't look.

557
00:17:45,839 --> 00:17:47,319
Turn around, yeah.

558
00:17:47,319 --> 00:17:48,199
Perfect.

559
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:49,560
Mouth closed.

560
00:17:49,560 --> 00:17:50,319
I'm locking eyes with Zhou Youling.

561
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:50,760
Mouth closed.

562
00:17:52,239 --> 00:17:53,040
Okay.

563
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:53,640
Cool.

564
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:54,560
He wanted to smile.

565
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:55,719
But you told him to close his mouth.

566
00:17:56,599 --> 00:17:58,520
You looked a bit spaced out just now.

567
00:17:58,520 --> 00:17:59,920
But I think this pose is good.

568
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:01,520
Seriously.

569
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:02,079
It's great.

570
00:18:02,079 --> 00:18:03,079
Every shot turns out amazing.

571
00:18:04,079 --> 00:18:04,719
Turn a bit.

572
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:07,119
A bit more.

573
00:18:07,119 --> 00:18:08,479
Actually, better without this.

574
00:18:08,479 --> 00:18:10,319
Nothing feels right with this.

575
00:18:10,319 --> 00:18:10,959
Forget it then.

576
00:18:10,959 --> 00:18:11,680
Another day.

577
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,280
Next time.

578
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:13,479
We'll find a better shot.

579
00:18:13,479 --> 00:18:14,520
And we'll lock eyes.

580
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,880
Who wants to drive next?

581
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:23,319
Liu.

582
00:18:23,319 --> 00:18:24,359
So how does this work?

583
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,199
Pull up to go forward.

584
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:27,439
Alright, got it.

585
00:18:28,319 --> 00:18:28,800
Turn back later.

586
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:29,479
I'll take control.

587
00:18:29,479 --> 00:18:30,319
Turn around up ahead.

588
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:32,479
Turn hard right.

589
00:18:32,479 --> 00:18:34,640
Full lock.

590
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:36,680
I thought you were controlling it
with your feet.

591
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:37,319
(Taking over urgently)
Full lock.

592
00:18:37,319 --> 00:18:38,000
Full lock.

593
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:41,839
You want to turn around?

594
00:18:41,839 --> 00:18:42,439
Yes, there.

595
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:43,760
Should we keep going?

596
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:44,280
Yes, go left.

597
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:46,000
Go left.

598
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:49,199
If you go straight,

599
00:18:49,199 --> 00:18:50,239
they'll be calling for you.

600
00:18:50,239 --> 00:18:51,599
Another kid driving now?

601
00:18:52,439 --> 00:18:53,280
Let the adults drive.

602
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,400
Don't let the kids steer.

603
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:58,640
Coming up to a narrow path.

604
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:00,520
Don't crash into others

605
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:02,160
or flip their kayak.

606
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:03,000
Send them flying.

607
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:04,479
Slow down.

608
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:07,920
It's fine.

609
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,640
Like this.

610
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:10,119
(Panicking)
Like this.

611
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:15,640
Zhou Youling is struggling.

612
00:19:17,439 --> 00:19:19,040
You guys drive like this too?

613
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:19,359
Yes.

614
00:19:19,959 --> 00:19:20,920
No, not at all.

615
00:19:27,359 --> 00:19:28,119
Be careful.

616
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:28,880
Watch out.

617
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:29,640
Did it hurt?

618
00:19:30,199 --> 00:19:30,599
No.

619
00:19:32,439 --> 00:19:33,880
Straighten up, good.

620
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:34,640
Just go straight.

621
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:35,959
Alright, go.

622
00:19:35,959 --> 00:19:37,719
Make a slight adjustment.

623
00:19:38,479 --> 00:19:39,199
There.

624
00:19:39,199 --> 00:19:40,400
Now I can take photos.

625
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:41,680
We can't crash
in such an open area, right?

626
00:19:43,079 --> 00:19:43,839
Not so sure.

627
00:19:43,839 --> 00:19:44,680
We're getting close.

628
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:00,199
Let's go.

629
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,680
The activities this afternoon

630
00:20:04,359 --> 00:20:04,959
feel

631
00:20:04,959 --> 00:20:06,160
so nostalgic.

632
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:08,040
I haven't done this for years.

633
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:10,439
It feels so close to nature.

634
00:20:10,439 --> 00:20:10,839
Yeah.

635
00:20:10,839 --> 00:20:11,800
Surrounded by water and greenery.

636
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:12,560
Yeah.

637
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:15,439
Yesterday,

638
00:20:15,439 --> 00:20:16,520
the carnival event

639
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:17,359
was pretty lively.

640
00:20:17,359 --> 00:20:18,400
It was full of life.

641
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,920
Back here now,

642
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,479
it's peaceful again.

643
00:20:25,359 --> 00:20:26,599
A good mix of action and calm.

644
00:20:26,599 --> 00:20:27,359
Indeed.

645
00:20:29,239 --> 00:20:31,880
Look at this. It's hilarious.

646
00:20:32,439 --> 00:20:34,239
So funny.

647
00:20:34,719 --> 00:20:35,119
Brother.

648
00:20:35,119 --> 00:20:36,520
Give us a wave, Brother.

649
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:37,040
Brother.

650
00:20:38,719 --> 00:20:39,400
Got it.

651
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:40,359
Wait.

652
00:20:40,359 --> 00:20:40,880
Don't you think

653
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:41,880
the wedding procession is funny?

654
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:43,319
The three-wheels in the village.

655
00:20:43,319 --> 00:20:44,040
Yeah.

656
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,239
So funny.

657
00:20:47,239 --> 00:20:48,680
So what is this today?

658
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:49,239
"Rural Love Story"?
